  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "To attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, you typically need to:\n\n1. Be a Berkshire Hathaway shareholder (either owning BRK.A or BRK.B stock)\n\n2. Obtain an admission ticket, which is usually:\n- Sent automatically to registered shareholders\n- Can be requested through the company's transfer agent\n- Proof of stock ownership is required\n\n3. The meeting is traditionally held in Omaha, Nebraska, usually in early May\n\n4. While historically open to all shareholders, tickets are limited and distributed on a first-come, first-served basis\n\n5. In recent years, the meeting has sometimes offered virtual attendance options\n\nThe event is often referred to as the \"Woodstock of Capitalism\" and typically features Warren Buffett and Charlie Munger answering shareholder questions for several hours.\n\nFor the most current and specific requirements, I recommend checking Berkshire Hathaway's official investor relations website or contacting their investor relations department directly, as details can change from year to year.",
